You are a senior full-stack architect and product engineer. Build a production-ready web platform for IELTS candidates to practice and take mock tests.

STACK REQUIREMENT (ZERO-COST / FREE TIER OPTIMIZED)
- Next.js 16+ with App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- shadcn/ui
- Prisma ORM
- Supabase (Use for PostgreSQL Database, File Storage, AND Auth to keep it in one ecosystem)
- pgvector (Enabled inside Supabase for vector embeddings / RAG)
- Redis + BullMQ (Use Upstash free tier for Redis)
- Stripe (Test mode for payments)
- Google Gemini API (Use for all AI generation, writing/speaking evaluation, and text embeddings via their free tier)
- Voice/Audio: Use Web Speech API natively in the browser for Text-to-Speech (AI interviewer). Use browser native SpeechRecognition OR Groq Whisper API for Speech-to-Text (student answers).

PROJECT NAME
AI IELTS Mock Test Platform
brand name: IELTS FLOW

PRODUCT GOAL
Create a complete IELTS mock test platform where candidates can:
1. Practice Reading, Listening, Writing, and Speaking
2. Take full-length timed mock tests
3. Receive AI-predicted band scores for Writing and Speaking
4. Take AI-based speaking mock interviews
5. Book instructor-led speaking mocks through scheduled meetings
6. Track progress, weaknesses, readiness, and improvement over time

A key feature is that the admin can upload PDFs and other materials, and the AI will use those resources as the base pattern to generate new practice tests and mock tests.

IMPORTANT PRODUCT RULES
- The platform should feel close to a real IELTS exam
- AI scores must be shown as predicted practice band scores, not official IELTS scores
- Feedback must be rubric-based and transparent
- All generated content should be original and inspired by uploaded materials, not copied
- System should support both AI speaking tests and live instructor speaking tests

BUILD OBJECTIVE
Create:
1. Scalable architecture
2. Clean folder structure
3. Full database schema
4. Admin dashboard
5. Student dashboard
6. Instructor dashboard
7. IELTS test engine
8. AI evaluation pipelines
9. Resource upload + RAG ingestion workflow
10. Meeting scheduling workflow
11. Subscription/payment flow
12. Modern high-trust UI

USER ROLES
- Guest
- Student
- Instructor
- Admin
- Super Admin

CORE FEATURES

1. PUBLIC WEBSITE
