2. STUDENT DASHBOARD
Build a dashboard with:
- Overview cards
- Latest predicted band
- Target band
- Exam readiness score
- Upcoming speaking sessions
- Practice history
- Skill progress charts
- Recommended next actions
- Weakness analysis
- Personalized study suggestions

3. TEST MODULES
**Question Navigation Panel**
   - Right-hand sidebar with clickable question numbers
   - Colors for status:
     - Gray: Not visited
     - Yellow: Visited, not answered
     - Green: Answered
     - Red: Flagged for review
   - Clicking a number scrolls/activates that question
-Add вЂњMark for ReviewвЂќ like the real exam.
A. LISTENING
- IELTS-style listening interface
- Audio player
- Section timing
- Multiple question types
- Auto-submit
- Review answers
- Score calculation
- Estimated band mapping

B. READING
- Passage and questions layout
- IELTS-style timing
- Multiple question types
- Highlight / note functionality
- Review mode
- Correct answer explanations
- Estimated band mapping

C. WRITING
Support:
- Task 1
- Task 2

Features:
- Timer
- Word count
- Autosave
- Submit for AI evaluation
- Store all drafts and attempts

AI writing evaluation should include:
- Task Achievement / Task Response
- Coherence & Cohesion
- Lexical Resource
- Grammatical Range & Accuracy
- Predicted band for each criterion
- Estimated overall band
- Strengths
- Weaknesses
- Sentence-level corrections
- Vocabulary improvement suggestions
- Better sample rewrite
- Examiner-style summary

D. SPEAKING
Two speaking types:

TYPE 1: AI SPEAKING MOCK
- AI interviewer simulates IELTS speaking test
- Part 1: personal questions
- Part 2: cue card with preparation timer
- Part 3: follow-up discussion
- Voice interaction
- Audio recording
- Speech-to-text transcription
- Save transcript and audio
- AI evaluation

Speaking evaluation should include:
- Fluency & Coherence
- Lexical Resource
- Grammatical Range & Accuracy
- Pronunciation
- Predicted score per criterion
- Estimated overall band
- Filler word analysis
- Pause/hesitation analysis
- Pronunciation feedback
- Vocabulary and grammar feedback
- Suggested better response strategy

TYPE 2: INSTRUCTOR SPEAKING MOCK
- Student can book live speaking session
- Instructor sets availability
- Student sees available slots
- Session booking flow
- Meeting link generation
- Instructor scoring form
- Rubric-based manual scoring
- Written instructor comments
- Compare instructor score vs AI score

4. ADMIN RESOURCE UPLOAD + AI GENERATION
Admin can upload:
- PDF
- DOCX
- TXT
- CSV
- Images with OCR
- Sample answers
- Cue cards
- Reading passages
- Writing prompts
- Lesson notes
- Vocabulary lists

System should:
- Upload and store files
- Extract text
- Chunk content
- Create embeddings
- Store in vector database
- Tag resources by:
